{{Biochemistry}} a [[polysaccharide]], [[glucose]] [[polymer]] resembling the [[starch]] in [[plant]]s (often termed "animal starch"), which is highly [[branch]]ed. It is formed of small chains of 8 to 12 glucose [[molecule]]s [[covalent]]ly linked together with alpha (1->4) bonds. These shorter chains are then [[covalent]]ly linked together with alpha (1->6) bonds. A single [[molecule]] of glycogen can be made of up to ~100,000 [[molecule]]s of [[glucose]].